### FME results
Model <- function(p,x) {
    vmax_0 <- 1.0815E11
    #ea_up <- 61.77 <- p[1]
    r <- 0.008314
    a <- 0.5
    ec <- 0.0325
    p[2] <- 0.0025 #km_c
    soc <- 144.5986
      x = x 
      vmax_c = vmax_0 * exp(-p[1] / (r * (x + 273))) #calculate depolymerization kinetics #y=vmax_c
      y = vmax_c * a * ec * soc / (p[2] + soc) #depolymerization of soc by enzymes
  return(data.frame(x,y)) #x = temp, y = decom_c
}
#Model(62,Obs$x)

## DREAM results
unloadNamespace("dream")
library(dream)

Model.y <- function(p,x) {
    vmax_0 <- 1.0815E11
    #ea_up <- 61.77 <- p[1]
    r <- 0.008314
    a <- 0.5
    ec <- 0.0325
    p[2] <- 0.0025 #km_c
    soc <- 144.5986
      vmax_c = vmax_0 * exp(-p[1] / (r * (x + 273))) #calculate depolymerization kinetics
      vmax_c * a * ec * soc / (p[2] + soc) #depolymerization of soc by enzymes
}

pars <- list(p1=c(0,100))#, p2=c(-200,100))

control <- list(
                nseq=4
                )

set.seed(456)
dd <- dreamCalibrate(FUN=Model.y,
                     pars=pars,
                     obs=dataUsedAll$y,
                     FUN.pars=list(x=dataUsedAll$x),
                     control=control
                     )
## R.stats:

## Calculate bounds around output estimates

plotCIs <- function(x,cis,...){
  em <- strwidth("M")/2
  segments(x0=x,y0=cis[,1],
           x1=x,y1=cis[,2],
           ...
           )
  segments(x0=x-em,y0=cis[,1],
           x1=x+em,y1=cis[,1],
           ...
           )
  segments(x0=x-em,y0=cis[,2],
           x1=x+em,y1=cis[,2],
           ...
           )
}##plotCIs
